25|$|Overview Many <b>urban</b> <b>water</b> and {{wastewater}} utilities in China experience financial stress, because user fees are set well below cost recovery levels and government subsidies are insufficient {{to cover the}} resulting gap. In 2004, 60% of <b>urban</b> <b>water</b> utilities reported negative net incomes. The financial situation of wastewater utilities {{is expected to be}} even more precarious. Tariffs have increased by 50% since 1998 and now stand at 1.5 RMB/m3 or US$0.20/m3. These rates are insufficient to cover costs.|$|E
